    <Overview>
    <Title>Virtue Ethics Test</Title>
  </Overview>
  <Overview>
     <FormattedContent>
      <![CDATA[
      In the Virtue Ethics HITs, you will write two similarly worded scenarios each demonstrating different character traits/virtues/vices (e.g., courage, envy, careless, easy to make angry).<br/>
      You will write the scenario demonstrating the character trait you choose to write about.<br/><br/>

      Example:<br/>
         a. While the family was walking in their neighborhood, they stayed on the sidewalk.<br/>
         b. While the family was walking in their neighborhood, they walked across people's yards.<br/><br/>

      Answer:<br/>
    	 a. Related Character Trait/Virtue/Vice: law abiding<br/>
         b. Related Character Trait/Virtue/Vice: disrepsectful<br/><br/>

      Select the correct character trait in the following scenarios.
      ]]>
    </FormattedContent>
  </Overview>

